        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 9:22PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 922 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Simonton Lake. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elkhart, Simonton Lake, Granger, Edwardsburg, Adamsville, Juno Lake,
and Eagle Lake.

This includes Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 84 and
92.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
